149
00:12:14,580 --> 00:12:16,130
You have to back me up on this.

150
00:12:16,130 --> 00:12:16,930
I understand.

151
00:12:17,600 --> 00:12:19,370
General Li kept those knives and forks

152
00:12:19,370 --> 00:12:20,600
not out of greed,

153
00:12:20,930 --> 00:12:21,560
but simply

154
00:12:21,560 --> 00:12:23,360
to bring them home as souvenirs.

155
00:12:23,930 --> 00:12:25,190
In the end, his pockets

156
00:12:25,440 --> 00:12:26,570
were full of butter.

157
00:12:28,560 --> 00:12:30,370
Come on, let's drink!

158
00:12:32,170 --> 00:12:32,800
Drink up!

159
00:12:32,800 --> 00:12:34,000
Drink, drink, drink!

160
00:12:44,820 --> 00:12:46,150
What was the joke about?

161
00:12:46,480 --> 00:12:47,480
Such a commotion.

162
00:12:48,480 --> 00:12:49,480
General Li here was sharing

163
00:12:49,480 --> 00:12:51,340
his thoughts on Western cuisine.

164
00:12:52,250 --> 00:12:53,130
What thoughts?

165
00:12:53,800 --> 00:12:54,560
General Li thinks

166
00:12:54,560 --> 00:12:55,800
the steak tastes excellent.

167
00:12:55,800 --> 00:12:57,260
One portion is not enough.

168
00:12:57,720 --> 00:12:58,320
Is that so?

169
00:12:59,640 --> 00:13:00,800
Here, have my portion

170
00:13:00,800 --> 00:13:01,480
as well.

171
00:13:03,440 --> 00:13:04,970
General Li, have some more.

172
00:13:16,250 --> 00:13:17,130
Viceroy.

173
00:13:18,210 --> 00:13:19,610
There aren't any changes

174
00:13:20,170 --> 00:13:22,300
for the autumn military drill, right?

175
00:13:28,530 --> 00:13:29,930
I just received news that

176
00:13:32,130 --> 00:13:34,260
there's an armed uprising in Wuchang.

177
00:13:36,860 --> 00:13:37,990
Wuchang and Hanyang

178
00:13:38,370 --> 00:13:41,300
have completely fallen into the hands of the rebels.

179
00:13:43,050 --> 00:13:44,130
All our telegraphic

180
00:13:44,130 --> 00:13:45,660
communications with Wuhan

181
00:13:46,100 --> 00:13:47,100
have been cut off.

182
00:13:56,820 --> 00:13:58,680
We've received an imperial order

183
00:13:58,980 --> 00:14:01,440
